history.content:
I just had this same issue. 

Math 110 has reserved seats for declared Math majors and undeclared students. If you are not one of these, you will be placed on the waitlist until Phase 2 or adjustment period. 

However, if you fall into that category (ie not declared math) and try to enroll in a section whose waitlist is full, then you will get that error  .

Try some different sections until you find one that fits your schedule and lets you enroll on the waitlist (if you are not declared stat major).

Hi I am trying to enroll in 110 but i get this:

Request not processed. There is no wait list available. The wait list request was not processed, as there are no wait list places available for one or more of the class sections in this request.

Can I still enroll?
history.subject: Trying to enroll in Math 110
